title: Products and fundamental groups
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Given two pointed spaces $$(X_1,x_1)$$ and $$(X_2,x_2),$$ we have
$$
\pi_1(X_1 \times X_2,(x_1,x_2)) \cong \pi_1(X_1,x_1) \times \pi_1(X_2,x_2).
$$
The same is true for arbitrary, even infinite products.